{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":772,"text":"I am a chef"},{"time":2336,"text":"and a food policy guy,"},{"time":4779,"text":"but I come from a whole\nfamily of teachers."},{"time":8096,"text":"My sister is a special ed\nteacher in Chicago."},{"time":11415,"text":"My father just retired\nafter 25 years teaching fifth grade."},{"time":16177,"text":"My aunt and uncle were professors."},{"time":18346,"text":"My cousins all teach."},{"time":20022,"text":"Everybody in my family, basically,\nteaches except for me."},{"time":24778,"text":"They taught me that the only way\nto get the right answers"},{"time":29646,"text":"is to ask the right questions."},{"time":33051,"text":"So what are the right questions"},{"time":34658,"text":"when it comes to improving\nthe educational outcomes for our children?"},{"time":40806,"text":"There's obviously\nmany important questions,"},{"time":43652,"text":"but I think the following\nis a good place to start:"},{"time":47046,"text":"What do we think the connection is"},{"time":49114,"text":"between a child's growing mind"},{"time":52557,"text":"and their growing body?"},{"time":54870,"text":"What can we expect our kids to learn"},{"time":57632,"text":"if their diets are full of sugar\nand empty of nutrients?"},{"time":62617,"text":"What can they possibly learn"},{"time":64822,"text":"if their bodies\nare literally going hungry?"},{"time":70157,"text":"And with all the resources\nthat we are pouring into schools,"},{"time":73988,"text":"we should stop and ask ourselves:"},{"time":76164,"text":"Are we really setting\nour kids up for success?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80119,"text":"Now, a few years ago,"},{"time":81848,"text":"I was a judge on a cooking\ncompetition called \"Chopped.\""},{"time":86598,"text":"Four chefs compete\nwith mystery ingredients"},{"time":89602,"text":"to see who can cook the best dishes."},{"time":93008,"text":"Except for this episode --\nit was a very special one."},{"time":97402,"text":"Instead of four overzealous chefs\ntrying to break into the limelight --"},{"time":100858,"text":"something that I would know\nnothing about --"},{"time":102949,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":104014,"text":"these chefs were school chefs;"},{"time":106697,"text":"you know, the women that you used\nto call \"lunch ladies,\""},{"time":109870,"text":"but the ones I insist\nwe call \"school chefs.\""},{"time":113303,"text":"Now, these women -- God bless\nthese women --"},{"time":116307,"text":"spend their day cooking\nfor thousands of kids,"},{"time":120264,"text":"breakfast and lunch,\nwith only $2.68 per lunch,"},{"time":124056,"text":"with only about a dollar of that\nactually going to the food."},{"time":128226,"text":"In this episode,"},{"time":130130,"text":"the main-course\nmystery ingredient was quinoa."},{"time":133400,"text":"Now, I know it's been a long time"},{"time":135085,"text":"since most of you have had a school lunch,"},{"time":137305,"text":"and we've made a lot\nof progress on nutrition,"},{"time":139941,"text":"but quinoa still is not a staple\nin most school cafeterias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143099,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144966,"text":"So this was a challenge."},{"time":146957,"text":"But the dish that I will never forget\nwas cooked by a woman"},{"time":150198,"text":"named Cheryl Barbara."},{"time":151879,"text":"Cheryl was the nutrition director"},{"time":153637,"text":"at High School in the Community\nin Connecticut."},{"time":156025,"text":"She cooked this delicious pasta."},{"time":158206,"text":"It was amazing."},{"time":159456,"text":"It was a pappardelle with Italian sausage,"},{"time":162123,"text":"kale, Parmesan cheese."},{"time":163919,"text":"It was delicious, like,\nrestaurant-quality good, except --"},{"time":167202,"text":"she basically just threw the quinoa,\npretty much uncooked,"},{"time":170986,"text":"into the dish."},{"time":172553,"text":"It was a strange choice,"},{"time":174297,"text":"and it was super crunchy."},{"time":176794,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":179460,"text":"So I took on the TV accusatory judge thing\nthat you're supposed to do,"},{"time":184402,"text":"and I asked her why she did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186794,"text":"Cheryl responded, \"Well, first,\nI don't know what quinoa is.\""},{"time":190137,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":191221,"text":"\"But I do know that it's a Monday,"},{"time":195261,"text":"and that in my school,\nat High School in the Community,"},{"time":198642,"text":"I always cook pasta.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":201116,"text":"See, Cheryl explained\nthat for many of her kids,"},{"time":204574,"text":"there were no meals on the weekends."},{"time":208728,"text":"No meals on Saturday."},{"time":212343,"text":"No meals on Sunday, either."},{"time":215047,"text":"So she cooked pasta\nbecause she wanted to make sure"},{"time":218537,"text":"she cooked something she knew\nher children would eat."},{"time":224760,"text":"Something that would stick\nto their ribs, she said."},{"time":228882,"text":"Something that would fill them up."},{"time":232972,"text":"Cheryl talked about how,\nby the time Monday came,"},{"time":237967,"text":"her kids' hunger pangs were so intense"},{"time":240592,"text":"that they couldn't even begin\nto think about learning."},{"time":244356,"text":"Food was the only thing on their mind."},{"time":250714,"text":"The only thing."},{"time":252296,"text":"And unfortunately, the stats --\nthey tell the same story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256071,"text":"So, let's put this\ninto the context of a child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260633,"text":"And we're going to focus on"},{"time":261963,"text":"the most important meal\nof the day, breakfast."},{"time":264231,"text":"Meet Allison."},{"time":265566,"text":"She's 12 years old,"},{"time":267094,"text":"she's smart as a whip"},{"time":268774,"text":"and she wants to be a physicist\nwhen she grows up."},{"time":271561,"text":"If Allison goes to a school\nthat serves a nutritious breakfast"},{"time":275594,"text":"to all of their kids,"},{"time":276864,"text":"here's what's going to follow."},{"time":278946,"text":"Her chances of getting a nutritious meal,"},{"time":282235,"text":"one with fruit and milk,\none lower in sugar and salt,"},{"time":285425,"text":"dramatically increase."},{"time":287637,"text":"Allison will have a lower rate\nof obesity than the average kid."},{"time":291344,"text":"She'll have to visit the nurse less."},{"time":293153,"text":"She'll have lower levels\nof anxiety and depression."},{"time":296196,"text":"She'll have better behavior."},{"time":297736,"text":"She'll have better attendance,\nand she'll show up on time more often."},{"time":301015,"text":"Why?"},{"time":302411,"text":"Well, because there's a good meal\nwaiting for her at school."},{"time":306007,"text":"Overall, Allison is in much better health"},{"time":309461,"text":"than the average school kid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311887,"text":"So what about that kid"},{"time":313544,"text":"who doesn't have a nutritious\nbreakfast waiting for him?"},{"time":316555,"text":"Well, meet Tommy."},{"time":318546,"text":"He's also 12. He's a wonderful kid."},{"time":320998,"text":"He wants to be a doctor."},{"time":322785,"text":"By the time Tommy is in kindergarten,"},{"time":324573,"text":"he's already underperforming in math."},{"time":328174,"text":"By the time he's in third grade,"},{"time":330378,"text":"he's got lower math and reading scores."},{"time":334158,"text":"By the time he's 11,"},{"time":335975,"text":"it's more likely that Tommy will have\nto have repeated a grade."},{"time":341092,"text":"Research shows that kids\nwho do not have consistent nourishment,"},{"time":344213,"text":"particularly at breakfast,"},{"time":345492,"text":"have poor cognitive function overall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350750,"text":"So how widespread is this problem?"},{"time":353676,"text":"Well, unfortunately, it's pervasive."},{"time":357228,"text":"Let me give you two stats"},{"time":358477,"text":"that seem like they're on opposite\nends of the issue,"},{"time":361465,"text":"but are actually two sides\nof the same coin."},{"time":364140,"text":"On the one hand,"},{"time":366178,"text":"one in six Americans are food insecure,"},{"time":369410,"text":"including 16 million children --\nalmost 20 percent --"},{"time":373394,"text":"are food insecure."},{"time":374808,"text":"In this city alone, in New York City,"},{"time":378173,"text":"474,000 kids under the age of 18\nface hunger every year."},{"time":384884,"text":"It's crazy."},{"time":386480,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":388503,"text":"diet and nutrition is the number one cause\nof preventable death and disease"},{"time":392636,"text":"in this country, by far."},{"time":395271,"text":"And fully a third of the kids\nthat we've been talking about tonight"},{"time":398516,"text":"are on track to have diabetes\nin their lifetime."},{"time":402807,"text":"Now, what's hard\nto put together but is true"},{"time":405213,"text":"is that, many times,\nthese are the same children."},{"time":408855,"text":"So they fill up on the unhealthy\nand cheap calories"},{"time":411778,"text":"that surround them in their communities\nand that their families can afford."},{"time":416752,"text":"But then by the end of the month,"},{"time":419757,"text":"food stamps run out\nor hours get cut at work,"},{"time":423346,"text":"and they don't have the money\nto cover the basic cost of food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428089,"text":"But we should be able\nto solve this problem, right?"},{"time":431439,"text":"We know what the answers are."},{"time":433917,"text":"As part of my work at the White House,\nwe instituted a program"},{"time":438072,"text":"that for all schools that had\n40 percent more low-income kids,"},{"time":441590,"text":"we could serve breakfast and lunch\nto every kid in that school."},{"time":446272,"text":"For free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448305,"text":"This program has been\nincredibly successful,"},{"time":450380,"text":"because it helped us overcome\na very difficult barrier"},{"time":454456,"text":"when it came to getting kids\na nutritious breakfast."},{"time":457625,"text":"And that was the barrier of stigma."},{"time":461769,"text":"See, schools serve\nbreakfast before school,"},{"time":467778,"text":"and it was only available\nfor the poor kids."},{"time":473371,"text":"So everybody knew who was poor\nand who needed government help."},{"time":477597,"text":"Now, all kids, no matter how much\nor how little their parents make,"},{"time":482421,"text":"have a lot of pride."},{"time":485107,"text":"So what happened?"},{"time":486977,"text":"Well, the schools that have\nimplemented this program"},{"time":489469,"text":"saw an increase in math and reading\nscores by 17.5 percent."},{"time":494657,"text":"17.5 percent."},{"time":497490,"text":"And research shows that when kids\nhave a consistent, nutritious breakfast,"},{"time":503882,"text":"their chances of graduating\nincrease by 20 percent."},{"time":508313,"text":"20 percent."},{"time":511012,"text":"When we give our kids\nthe nourishment they need,"},{"time":514795,"text":"we give them the chance to thrive,"},{"time":517955,"text":"both in the classroom and beyond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520900,"text":"Now, you don't have to trust me on this,"},{"time":524644,"text":"but you should talk to Donna Martin."},{"time":527249,"text":"I love Donna Martin."},{"time":529020,"text":"Donna Martin is the school nutrition\ndirector at Burke County"},{"time":532721,"text":"in Waynesboro, Georgia."},{"time":535053,"text":"Burke County is one\nof the poorest districts"},{"time":537790,"text":"in the fifth-poorest state in the country,"},{"time":540517,"text":"and about 100 percent of Donna's students\nlive at or below the poverty line."},{"time":547672,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":548907,"text":"Donna decided to get out ahead\nof the new standards that were coming,"},{"time":552885,"text":"and overhaul her nutrition standards."},{"time":556200,"text":"She improved and added\nfruit and vegetables and whole grains."},{"time":560875,"text":"She served breakfast in the classroom\nto all of her kids."},{"time":564374,"text":"And she implemented a dinner program."},{"time":566222,"text":"Why?"},{"time":568336,"text":"Well, many of her kids didn't have\ndinner when they went home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571975,"text":"So how did they respond?"},{"time":574208,"text":"Well, the kids loved the food."},{"time":577577,"text":"They loved the better nutrition,"},{"time":579289,"text":"and they loved not being hungry."},{"time":582759,"text":"But Donna's biggest supporter\ncame from an unexpected place."},{"time":587055,"text":"His name from Eric Parker,"},{"time":589163,"text":"and he was the head football coach\nfor the Burke County Bears."},{"time":593668,"text":"Now, Coach Parker had coached\nmediocre teams for years."},{"time":596757,"text":"The Bears often ended\nin the middle of the pack --"},{"time":599704,"text":"a big disappointment in one\nof the most passionate football states"},{"time":602890,"text":"in the Union."},{"time":604542,"text":"But the year Donna changed the menus,"},{"time":609174,"text":"the Bears not only won their division,"},{"time":612705,"text":"they went on to win\nthe state championship,"},{"time":615168,"text":"beating the Peach County Trojans"},{"time":617558,"text":"28-14."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618904,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621283,"text":"And Coach Parker,"},{"time":623507,"text":"he credited that championship\nto Donna Martin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629274,"text":"When we give our kids\nthe basic nourishment,"},{"time":632059,"text":"they're going to thrive."},{"time":634310,"text":"And it's not just\nup to the Cheryl Barbaras"},{"time":637374,"text":"and the Donna Martins of the world."},{"time":640039,"text":"It's on all of us."},{"time":642218,"text":"And feeding our kids the basic nutrition\nis just the starting point."},{"time":647517,"text":"What I've laid out is really a model"},{"time":649506,"text":"for so many of the most pressing\nissues that we face."},{"time":654183,"text":"If we focus on the simple goal\nof properly nourishing ourselves,"},{"time":660514,"text":"we could see a world\nthat is more stable and secure;"},{"time":664929,"text":"we could dramatically improve\nour economic productivity;"},{"time":669023,"text":"we could transform our health care"},{"time":672736,"text":"and we could go a long way"},{"time":674436,"text":"in ensuring that the Earth can provide\nfor generations to come."},{"time":677506,"text":"Food is that place\nwhere our collective efforts"},{"time":682198,"text":"can have the greatest impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685825,"text":"So we have to ask ourselves:\nWhat is the right question?"},{"time":688934,"text":"What would happen"},{"time":690486,"text":"if we fed ourselves more nutritious,\nmore sustainably grown food?"},{"time":696702,"text":"What would be the impact?"},{"time":699184,"text":"Cheryl Barbara,"},{"time":701909,"text":"Donna Martin,"},{"time":703555,"text":"Coach Parker and the Burke County Bears --"},{"time":706539,"text":"I think they know the answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708207,"text":"Thank you guys so very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709842,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}